properties.name: CLIENT_ID
properties.description: The system account identifier associated with attribute set

properties.name: CUSTOMER_ID
properties.description: Extracted from subscriber_key, null if equals to email_address

properties.name: SEND_ID
properties.description: Identifier associated to an email send

properties.name: SUBSCRIBER_ID
properties.description: The subscriber ID for the affected subscriber. This number represents the unique ID for each subscriber record

properties.name: SUBSCRIBER_KEY
properties.description: The subscriber key for the affected subscriber

properties.name: EMAIL_ADDRESS
properties.description: Customer''s email address. This column is anonymised

properties.name: EMAIL_DOMAIN
properties.description: Customer''s email domain. This column is anonymised case the number of unique users per domain is smaller thant 50

properties.name: TRIGGERED_SEND_EXTERNAL_KEY
properties.description: External key associated to a triggered send definition if the bounce resulted from a triggered send request

properties.name: BATCH_ID
properties.description: The batch ID number for any batches used in the send

properties.name: EVENT_TIMESTAMP
properties.description: The date timestamp the send took place

properties.name: EVENT_TYPE
properties.description: Identifier for the event type: Send

properties.name: CAMPAIGN_ID
properties.description: Identifier associated to a campaign. The use of campaign_id is not recommended due to lack of documentation

views.name: GEO_DIMENSION
views.selectStatement:
SELECT
    concat(ed.bob_entity_code, '-',gd.postcode) sk_geo,
    ed.bob_entity_code,
    ed.country,
    gd.country iso,
    gd.postcode zipcode,
    gd.language,
    gd.region_1,
    gd.region_1_type,
    gd.region_2,
    gd.region_2_type,
    gd.region_3,
    gd.region_3_type,
    gd.region_4,
    gd.region_4_type,
    gd.latitude,
    gd.longitude,
    gd.iso2,
    gd.timezone,
    gd.utc,
    gd.inserted_at
 FROM
      LANDING.MAT_GEO_DIMENSION_RAW gd
 INNER JOIN
          LANDING.MAT_ENTITY_DIMENSION ed
 ON
     (gd.country = regexp_replace(ed.country,'UK','GB')
          AND
      coalesce(ed.bob_entity_code,'null') != 'null')
